This paper deals with game theory and its application to analyzing the Nash equilibrium of asymmetric games. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also discusses the evolutionary dynamics of the simpler counterpart games, which suggests a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves analyzing the structure of games, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves mathematical analysis and formal relationships, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
